<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 12344/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Gregory</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-01"><hi rend="italic">May 1,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 9, Honduranean series.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your serial No. 9 of March 20,
                            1908, Honduranean series, relating to whether the Honduranean Government
                            would be willing, as an act of comity, to surrender fugitives from the
                            justice of the United States, charged with embezzlement, pending
                            negotiations between the Governments of the United States and Honduras
                            for an extradition treaty, I have the honor to inform you that the
                            Honduranean Government will grant extradition of fugitives if the crime
                            is of recent date and the party or parties not Honduraneans.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. H. Gregory</hi>,
                            Jr.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>